This plugin need some preparations before working:

Python packages:
You need the following packages
- OAuth2: http://github.com/simplegeo/python-oauth2
- SimpleJson: http://cheeseshop.python.org/pypi/simplejson
- Twitter: http://code.google.com/p/python-twitter/

Twitter-Account:
You need a twitter acount. And you need four different tokens so that this
plugin can login to your accoung. Therefor go to
https://dev.twitter.com/apps/new to create a new app. Fill out the fields with
the red star. Go to settings and change the permissions from "read only" to
"read and write". Go back to details and click on create access token. Now you
have to take all this tokens and write them into the twitter.xml file.

A tutorial with screenshots:
http://www.bmamba.de/?p=252

B3:
Now you have to copy the twitter.py file to extplugins/ and twitter.xml to
extplugins/conf/. Finally you need a new line in your b3.xml, something like:
<plugin config="@b3/extplugins/conf/b3twitter.xml" name="b3twitter" />

